      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUN FOREST RUN NZ (4) is a newcomer to the Alex Ashwood yard and enjoys a class drop on what he faced first up in Brisbane. Yet to win in four Australian starts but did manage a fourth at Menangle last time in. This looks a winnable assignment. GOLDEN SKIES (3) had enough speed to lead from a couple of spots wider and proved too good at her latest appearance at Ballarat, scoring by 2 metres. Can push forward again from this draw. Major player. EL BRAVO (9) continues a run of second line draws but was good when beaten only 3.5m after breaking last start. Race fit now and is a chance with manners. QUAKE PROOF (5) hasn't been far away of late and can be competitive in this line-up.",
